hoodMarket: The Northern Chicago area includes some of Chicago’s most historic and desirable neighborhoods, such as Lakeview, Edgewater, Uptown and Lincoln Park. The western portion of this corridor was historically zoned exclusively for manufacturing, but changes in Chicago’s zoning policy opened much of this land to multifamily and office uses. The result is a mix of housing, office, and industrial uses within this diverse and dynamic area of Chicago. The eastern portion of the area boasts one of the highest population densities in the Chicago region, while the western portion includes most of the area’s manufacturing and warehouse stock. ,Manufacturers and logistics companies are drawn to this area in part due to its accessibility, with its well-connected network of interstates providing access to over 10 million people and one of the nation’s busiest ports. The area’s small and mid-sized manufacturing companies benefit from the area’s dense, infill location and span across a variety of industries, including durable and non-durable goods wholesaling, commercial printing, HVAC, plumbing, and construction, ,Millions of square feet of industrial space have been demolished in North Chicago over the past decade, as many industrial owners capitalized on quickly rising land values by selling to multifamily and office developers. The decline in available space, coupled with steady tenant demand, pushed vacancy to near historic lows. In recognition of Chicago’s growing manufacturing activity, together with the area’s appealing last-mile distribution location, North Chicago is expected to continue to attract both large and small industrial tenants.
propOverview: Nestled on the border of Galewood and Belmont-Cragin in Northwest Side Chicago, Austin 1900 Building offers flexibility for almost any business and a location easy to reach for commuters. 5 minutes from W North Avenue, drivers can reach destinations like River North or O’Hare International Airport in around 30 minutes, traffic permitting. There is ample parking on-site for those commuting by car, but Austin 1900 Building also offers superb connectivity to public transit. The Galewood Metra Station is a 10-minute walk from the building and services the Milwaukee District West train line, which takes riders east to Union Station in around 40 minutes or as far west as Big Timber, past Elgin, in around 72. Buses on route 86 run along Narragansett Avenue and route 91 is on N Austin Avenue. The property stretches between these two major roads, making it easy to reach either. Across from the building is Amundsen Park, which has a new track and field providing recreation options to employees. Brickyard Mall is the premier retail destination in the area and only a 5-minute drive from the building. The center is home to grocery, fitness, and plenty of shopping and dining options from notable brands. Austin 1900 Building itself consists of three parcels. The first is 1900 N Austin Ave, an approximately 700,000 square foot office, research and development, and warehouse building. The second two parcels are both vacant land sites to either side of the building, approximately 6 acres to the west and 10 to the east. The offices on the south and east side offer breathtaking views of Amundsen Park and beyond to the Chicago skyline. The interior features a modern lobby, and flexibility between open offices, event spaces, space for research and development, and warehouse units with loading docks and drive-in doors. Energy-efficient improvements are in place, including the installation of LED lighting and a solar array that has been running since 2011.

hoodMarket: Sylmar is the northernmost neighborhood in the sprawling City of Los Angeles. Its distance from the area’s premiere employment and residential hubs give the area a suburban feel, but interstates 5, 405, and 210, collectively some of Los Angeles’ most heavily traveled highways, converge here. Interstate 5 is California’s main north-south artery and continues on into the Central Valley, while Interstate 210 offers direct access to the Inland Empire’s vast industrial landscape.,Manufacturing has been a staple of the area since the 1970s, with companies like L-3 Ocean Systems, Abbot/St. Jude Medical, and PPG Aerospace maintaining significant manufacturing operations here. While overall manufacturing employment has been declining in Los Angeles for decades, the growth of the logistics sector has helped offset those losses. ,The area’s strategic location at the conjunction of several major highways helps underpin strong demand for industrial space. New industrial development is minimal though, a common refrain across Los Angeles County.
propOverview: Located in Los Angeles’s northernmost neighborhood, 15148 Bledsoe Street in Sylmar, California, provides an excellent corporate image and location. Initially constructed in 1969, the entire building was renovated in 2015, and Unit B features office space with modern finishes and all the industrial amenities necessary for today’s industrial businesses. The 3,767 square-foot office overlooks the warehouse area and features offices and a conference room with attractive floor-to-ceiling glass partitions. The warehouse area features clear heights ranging from 14’-18’, 4 (four) covered truck well loading positions and 3 (three) ground level doors, and 1000-amps of 480-volt, 3-phase, 4-wire power throughout. The property provides multiple, convenient distribution options with only a 5-minute drive to the 5 and 210 freeways and a 10-minute drive to the 118, 405, and 14 freeways. The Bob Hope Airport can be reached in an 18-minute drive and the Los Angeles International Airport is just 35 minutes away, the Port of Long Beach is only 40 miles away, and the UP- Los Angeles rail line is only 21.6 miles from the property. For employees, the Sylmar/San Fernando Commuter Rail (Antelope Valley Line) is a 6-minute drive away, and the property is surrounded by densely packed residential neighborhoods. For shopping, dining, and conveniences, the Sylmar Towne Shopping Center is 6 minutes away and is surrounded by the bustling commercial district at the intersection of Hubbard Street and Glenoaks Boulevard.

Take part in creating the perfect commercial space for your company!
We work closely with our tenants to help our tenant's build the perfect space to suit their needs (prices vary depending upon buildout).

The space available shown below is 5,150 square feet. 
It includes access to a 16’ x 8’ freight elevator which leads to two available common loading docs on the first floor. 
There are two common bathroom located in the lobby of the building, however it is also possible to add bathrooms into the available space. 
We are finishing out an electric build out that will supply 400 amps of three phase power to the floor if necessary for the tenant. 
There is an additional 12,500 square feet available on upper floors if the tenant were ever decide to expand or in need of additional storage.
- Loading dock that leads onto a freight elevator.
- Freight Elevator leads to each floor.
- There are 10 ft. high ceilings.
- We have two free gated parking lots.
- The space contains windows that allow natural sunlight. Tenant has the option to include more windows for an additional cost.

Centrally located within the Philadelphia metropolitan area and its population of over 6 million residents, Northeast Philadelphia is a prime location for business serving not just the Philadelphia area, but the broader mid-Atlantic region. ,Intersate95 runs straight through Northeast Philadelphia, making New York City a 90-minute drive away. Forty percent of the U.S. population is also reachable within a day’s drive. Meanwhile, the Port of Philadelphia and Northeast Philadelphia International Airport are both roughly 20-minute drives from most of Northeast Philadelphia’s office and industrial parks.,Cardone Industries, one of the world’s largest auto parts remanufacturers, operates a 1 million square foot manufacturing facility in Northeast Philadelphia, and TJ Maxx maintains a 1 million square foot distribution facility. Food and beverage distributors including Pepsi, Quaker Valley Foods, and Dietz & Watson also have major operations here. Top local office tenants span a range of industries and include the Philadelphia Federal Credit Union, PCI Pharma Service, and Einstein Medical Center. ,Quick access to the region’s major cities and more affordable rents than those in Center City Philadelphia also make Northeast Philadelphia an attractive location for startups and contractor serving the areas major distribution, healthcare, and financial services employers.

spaceSummary:
LogistiCenterSM at Dallas is a modern bulk distribution center located in the Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex with great accessibility, making it well suited for both local and regional and national distribution. It is ideally located less than one mile from the full I-20 interchange on Bonnie View Rd, with easy access to Interstate 35, Interstate 30, Interstate 45, and State Highway 360. Also, close proximity to FedEx Ground Hub provides late drop-off ability and to UP Intermodal Facility provides lowest drayage costs. 

The South Dallas submarket currently has over 53 Million square feet of industrial space and is the fastest growing submarket in the Metroplex. The majority of the properties are institutionally owned and leased to a variety of e-commerce, distribution, warehouse, and assembly companies. South Dallas submarket is located along Interstate 20 and is just south of Dallas CBD. It is home to users such as Quaker Oats, Proctor & Gamble, Home Depot, Georgia Pacific, Whirlpool and many others.

propOverview: 10015 Waples Court is located in Sorrento Valley which was originally designed as San Diego's industrial district and paved the way for several well-known corporations and industries to headquarter there, such as Qualcomm, Dexcom, Arena Pharmaceuticals, and Accelrys US. Due to the short 15-minute drive to the University of California in San Diego, Sorrento Valley organically strayed from the original growth plan and has since become a desirable destination for residents, which provides businesses with a strong industrial infrastructure and a built-in labor force. Recognized as one of the leading high-tech hubs in the US, San Diego’s innovation economy is anchored by established companies such as Intel, Sony, and Hewlett Packard. San Diego is home to the largest concentration of military in the world, the largest federal military workforce in the nation, and some of the world’s largest research and development companies. Given the highly-skilled workforce, robust training programs, and proximity to Mexico, San Diego is also a hub for advanced manufacturing companies. In addition, the 1,100 life sciences companies and more than 80 research institutes are major drivers of the innovative local economy. 10015 Waples Court is located a half-mile off Mira Mesa Boulevard, the main thoroughfare through the industrial parks of Sorrento Valley, and provides easy access to major transportation routes with a 5-minute drive to I-805 and 10 minutes to I-5. The Port of San Diego is a 30-minute drive and oversees two major cargo terminals, the 96-acre Tenth Avenue Marine Terminal and the 135-acre National City Marine Terminal. 10015 Waples Court is under new ownership with modernizing renovations underway featuring 9,200 square feet of new, highly upgraded office space, 12 large grade-level doors, 9 dock positions, ESFR sprinkler system, and skylights. The facility boasts 31'-33' clear heights and 1,200 amps of 277/480 volt power with a 3-phase/4-wire system.

propOverview:
Highly Secure, Light Industrial Warehouse has up to 14,500 available square feet, 2 Street/Grade Level Roll-Up 16 foot-high clearance doors, 1600 amps of Electrical, Automated Sprinkler System and an exterior Roof "Membrane" that reflects 85% of sunlight and heat - keeping the interior of the building extremely comfortable and providing year round Climate Control. There is also 1000 square feet of Office Space with HVAC, two separate exterior entrances. 
Fantastic Location-conveniently located very close to downtown San Diego, just off Interstate 5 for easy Freeway Access all over San Diego County as well as a short 15 minute drive to the International Border to Mexico.
This Warehouse offers an exceptional Security System that includes Closed Circuit Monitoring and Alarm. Comprehensive WiFi is available throughout the building. There is a very large side yard that is gated and secure, offering the ability for deliveries to the side entrance with a high clearance, Roll Up door. Parking is also available both in the side yard as well as within the interior of the building. Two large, ADA compliant Bathrooms-one includes Shower and a Kitchen/Break area that offers a Refrigerator, Microwave as well as space for a Dining Table and Chairs. 
There are also Six (6) fully functional, individual Trailers (complete with Electrical, A/C, etc.) that are also available (if desired) and may be moved inside, outside or to another location. They are 8' x 8' x 18'L in size that can be used for laboratories, additional Storage, Private Offices and more.  
Public Transportation, Commuter Rail, Freight & Air Travel is readily available in the immediate area.

spaceSummary:
This highly secure, updated, Light Industrial Warehouse has 11,200 square feet of Floor Space, complete with HVAC, 2 street level Roll-Up high clearance doors, 1600 amps of Electrical, a fully automated Sprinkler System and high ceilings (except under the Mezzanine area, which offers another 3,500 square feet of possible space currently rented month to month). There is 1500 square feet of Office Space with two separate exterior entrances available and offering an additional 400 square feet of open space above the office space that is not counted in the rent-able square footage (free bonus space)! Conveniently located close to downtown San Diego, just off Interstate 5 for easy Freeway Access all over San Diego County!
In addition, there are also 5 to 6 individual “Trailers”  that are enclose-able, secure-able and complete with Air Conditioning and Electrical, approximately 200 square feet each and could be used on the interior or exterior of the Property as Laboratories, Independent Space for separate Vendors, Construction Storage, additional office space and a multitude of other purposes! They can also be removed from the Property if the Tenant has no use for these items. A large, ADA compliant Bathroom, located towards the rear of the building, also includes a full size Shower! There is a Kitchen area that offers a Full-Size Refrigerator, Microwave as well as space for a Dining Table and Chairs. A Forklift, with a 1 to 2 person cage, will also be provided for the convenience of the new Tenant!
This Highly Secure environment offers an exceptional Security System that includes Closed Circuit TV Monitoring both on location and off. The Warehouse has comprehensive and effective WiFi available throughout the building. There is also a very large side yard that is gated and secure, offering the ability for deliveries to the side entrance, high clearance Roll Up door. Parking is available both in the side yard as well as within the interior of the building however, it is somewhat limited outside the property. 
Public Transportation, Commuter Rail, Freight & Air Travel is readily available in the immediate area:
1.	Barrio Logan (Blue Line) Stop located just a short 6 blocks from the Property
2.	Harborside Transit Stop (also Blue Line) approximately 7 blocks away from the Property
3.	Commercial & 25th Transit Stop (Orange Line) approximately 7 blocks away from the Property
4.	San Diego Commuter Rail, Santa Fe Station (Coaster) located 2.7 miles away from the Property
5.	San Diego International Airport is located 4.6 miles from the Property
6.	Port of San Diego is located 1.2 miles from the Property

This space could also be a great location for antique dealers.

spaceSummary: "2431 E Van Buren is a former Deer–O Salsa manufacturing building, with many use opportunities. The property is located on the corner of 24th St Place and Van Buren across the street from the Arizona State Hospital Facility, Arizona State Prison Complex. The property is also less than 1000ft from the Light Rail stop at Washington and 24th St, and located within a federal Opportunity Zone, eligible for the benefits of such zoning.     The property is of solid brick construction, flat foam roof, fire sprinklers throughout, with a small gated yard area. The property also has 5 private restrooms, showers, a small kitchen, 6 private offices, and various larger open areas that would serve well as office space, or production areas. The property has HVAC cooling throughout.     The property is currently zoned C-3 one of the most diverse and accommodating zoning districts in the city which allows uses from automotive, dance halls, cabinet shops, cold storage, manufacturing, equipment rental, food processing, grocery, hardware, storage, office, administrative, retail sales, machine shops, pet care including animal housing, plant nursery, private clubs, restaurant, bars and lounges, school, fabrication, and wholesale.     If operated as a retail building the property has easy access to bus stops, light rail stops, and other public transit. The property has retail frontage on a main road. The property is located centrally in the valley with easy access to freeways and downtown Phoenix. Demographics in this area are focused in the lower income brackets.     If operated as an office property, the 2 levels of space and large open areas would serve any tenancy well in an open, loft like, office environment with 6 private offices, a small kitchen.     If operated as an industrial building, the property has a secure yard, 4 large openings for moving things in and out, and one large room with 16ft clear height ceilings"  Owner is open to medical marijuana uses including dispensary, and growing facilities.

spaceSummary:
1040 East Indian School Road is an ideal Live/Work opportunity that lies in the path-of-progress that is transitioning this Central Phoenix neighborhood. The property was extensively renovated in 2019 to include new paint, roof, windows, flooring, HVAC system, water heater, security lighting, stove/dishwasher and skylights in the warehouse.

This multi-functional property sits on the major arterial road of  Indian School Road between 7th Street and 12th Street in Central Phoenix. State Route 51  is less than a mile to the east, and the main Veterans Administration hospital is less than a quarter mile to the west. The property is contiguous to a very successful alternative lifestyle bar to the west, and across the street to the south lies the Blues bar the Rhythm Room. Much redevelopment can be observed along Indian School Road to the east and it is safe to say that the property is the path of a redevelopment wave in the future.

spaceSummary:
Constructed in 1987 by Sun State Builders, this 50,000 Sq. ft. freestanding building is located just south of West Van Buren Street between 43rd Avenue and 51st Avenue in Phoenix, Arizona. 
This convenient location is one mile south of Interstate 10 which offers a full four way diamond interchange at 35th Avenue, 43rd Avenue and 51st Avenue. The property is three miles from Interstate 17 and two miles from the new Loop 202 Freeway near 59th Avenue. The building is located in the affordable Riverside School Tax District and the property taxes are .08 SF for 2019. The building will be available for occupancy in November 2019. The owner has spent $250,000 for a new high quality roof covering earlier this year, and $107,000 for all new (17) evaporative coolers. The existing offices will be upgraded and the parking lot will have a new coating this fall.
